/issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Karl Wettin","active":true},"created":"2007-01-26T14:31:06.642+0000","updated":"2007-01-26T14:31:06.642+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12361328/comment/12467832","id":"12467832","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sqisher","name":"sqisher","emailAddress":"db at wazap dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel Bechler","active":true},"body":"That's what I heared from Matthias, too. (We work in the same company.) There were no problems with earlier versions of Lucene 2.1.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sqisher","name":"sqisher","emailAddress":"db at wazap dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Daniel Bechler","active":true},"created":"2007-01-26T14:36:25.425+0000","updated":"2007-01-26T14:36:25.425+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12361328/comment/12467838","id":"12467838","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"body":"OK, here's a quick unit test that catches the regression:\r\n\r\n    public void testSerializable() throws IOException {\r\n        Directory dir = new RAMDirectory();\r\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\r\n        ObjectOutput out = new ObjectOutputStream(bos);\r\n        out.writeObject(dir);\r\n        out.close();\r\n    }\r\n\r\nUsing this I tracked down the commit that caused serializability to break:\r\n\r\n    http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/lucene/java/trunk/src/java/org/apache/lucene/store/RAMDirectory.java?p2=%2Flucene%2Fjava%2Ftrunk%2Fsrc%2Fjava%2Forg%2Fapache%2Flucene%2Fstore%2FRAMDirectory.java&p1=%2Flucene%2Fjava%2Ftrunk%2Fsrc%2Fjava%2Forg%2Fapache%2Flucene%2Fstore%2FRAMDirectory.java&r1=478014&r2=478013&view=diff&pathrev=478014\r\n\r\nThis commit was for LUCENE-709","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"created":"2007-01-26T15:05:51.685+0000","updated":"2007-01-26T15:05:51.685+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12361328/comment/12468014","id":"12468014","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"body":"Alas, it looks like HashMap.keySet() and .values() are just not serializable, and never will be:\r\n\r\n    http://bugs.sun.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4501848\r\n\r\nI think keeping serialization for RAMDirectory is important.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mikemccand","name":"mikemccand","emailAddress":"lucene at mikemccandless dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael McCandless","active":true},"created":"2007-01-27T12:23:49.011+0000","updated":"2007-01-27T12:23:49.011+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12361328/comment/12468059","id":"12468059","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hossman","name":"hossman","emailAddress":"hossman_apachejira at fucit dot org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=hossman&avatarId=21247","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/usera